Pre-Game Insights: The New York Mets host the Los Angeles Dodgers on Friday in Game 5 of the NLCS. The Dodgers lead the series 3-1 and can move on to the World Series with a victory.
The Mets are 46-35 at home and 89-73 overall. Mets hitters are batting a collective.246, which ranks seventh in the NL.
The Dodgers have a 46-35 record in road games and a 98-64 record overall. Dodgers hitters are batting a collective.258, which ranks third in the NL.
The teams meet Friday for the 11th time this season. The Dodgers lead the season series 7-3.
